Well ive been pretty busy lately...graduating from highschool on tuesday and it doesnt feel like it at all. You think your gonna see the same people u have seen for the last 4 years of your life and your not. After all of this everything will change and everyone will go their seperate ways out into the real world. Social statuses mean nothing anymore...its so weird how this all works out. You work throughout all of highschool to try to be popular and be in the "IN" crowd and everything only for it to go away when u graduate then you have to do it all again at college if you go or if u dont it doesnt matter anymore...at all. I guess thats why its kinda weird when u think about how everyone bases their life on popularity and clothes and stuff...i dont but i look at all these kids at our school and i think that. Well anyways im excited. My parents gave me $1500 towards my new car for grad...ill be getting the car on Wednesday i believe becuz some retard burned his eyes using a welder without a mask haha..but its good hes ok. Anyways this summer should be fun...going to the beach a lot def and hanging out a lot of cool people should be daily rituals haha. Working will suck as usual but hey its life u know u gotta grow up and get used to it sometime haha.

OH WHAT A GAME!!! Soooo much fun!!! Dover stomped Spaulding bad haha (Corinne>>>owned..but i still <3 you anyways haha). There were so many people at that game it was hard to move around lol.
